name: (1,2-dibromoethyl)benzene

The addition of an ethyl group typically raises the melting point due to increased molecular weight and van der Waals forces, by approximately +20 °C. Each bromine atom is also relatively large and heavy, and its introduction tends to increase melting points further due to the increased polarizability and stronger intermolecular attractions; for each bromine, we can conservatively add about +24 °C to the melting point.
